app.boxmate

Class Showing

  • java.lang.Object
    • app.boxmate.Showing

  • public class Showing
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a showing of a show (i.e. if the show is being played more than once).
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Version:
    1.0.0 (24/05/2012)
    Author:
    Jonathan Tan

       java.util.ArrayList<Ticket> tickets)
        A constructor for the Showing class that requires the user/program to specify all the attributes as parameters.
        Parameters:
        date - The date of this showing.
        time - The time that the show begins.
        doorsOpen - The time the doors open for the show.
        seatsMax - The maximum number of seats that can be sold.
        seatsLeft - The number of seats left for sale.
        theatre - The venue for the showing.
        tickets - A list of all tickets that are for this showing.
